President Biden hosted President Zelenskyy of Ukraine at the White House, reaffirming US support for Ukraine's defense against Russian aggression. They discussed Ukraine's counteroffensive and the US announced a new package of security assistance, including air defense capabilities and Abrams tanks. The US also plans to host a conference in the fall to explore joint ventures and co-production in Ukraine's defense industry. The leaders also discussed support for Ukraine's energy sector and economic recovery, including efforts to increase energy generation and transmission capacity. President Zelenskyy shared plans to address corruption in Ukraine, and President Biden emphasized the importance of strong anti-corruption institutions. President Biden also welcomed President Zelenskyy's diplomatic efforts for a just and lasting peace.